episodes.title: The Light Bulb Scene
episodes.plot: BoJack has misgivings about his new show. Princess Carolyn visits an adoption agency. Todd interviews for a job at WhatTimeIsItRightNow.com.

episodes.title: The Dog Days Are Over
episodes.plot: Diane divorces Mr. Peanutbutter and moves into a shabby studio. Feeling melancholy, she travels to Vietnam to get away from it all.

episodes.title: Planned Obsolescence
episodes.plot: Todd meet's Yolanda's parents, who don't know she's asexual. Mr. Peanutbutter romances a young waitress. Gina confesses a childhood dream to BoJack.

episodes.title: BoJack the Feminist
episodes.plot: When Princess Carolyn casts a disgraced celeb in "Philbert," BoJack inadvertently takes a stand. Mr. Peanutbutter tries to toughen up his image.

episodes.title: The Amelia Earhart Story
episodes.plot: Painful memories come rushing back when Princess Carolyn visits her hometown and meets a pregnant teen. A stunt goes awry on the "Philbert" set.

episodes.title: Free Churro
episodes.plot: BoJack delivers a eulogy at a funeral.

episodes.title: INT. SUB
episodes.plot: Diane's therapist encourages her to set boundaries with BoJack. A missing string cheese ignites a dispute between Todd and Princess Carolyn.

episodes.title: Mr. Peanutbutter's Boos
episodes.plot: At BoJack's 25th annual Halloween party, Pickles gets a crash course in Mr. Peanutbutter's romantic history -- and some advice from Diane.

episodes.title: Ancient History
episodes.plot: A visiting Hollyhock dumps BoJack's painkillers, sending him on a desperate search for more. Todd tries to solve Emily's dating dilemma.

episodes.title: Head in the Clouds
episodes.plot: At the "Philbert" premiere party, Princess Carolyn deftly negotiates a deal, Gina steps into the limelight, and Diane confronts BoJack.

episodes.title: The Showstopper
episodes.plot: "Philbert" is a hit, and filming begins on Season 2. But as BoJack spirals deeper into addiction, he loses his grip on reality.

episodes.title: The Stopped Show
episodes.plot: In the midst of the latest PR crisis, Princess Carolyn gets a life-changing opportunity. With Diane's help, BoJack finally faces the music.
